<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1436,834,1111]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,834,859]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doderlein" authorityYear="1916" box="[295,442,834,859]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" genus="Monachaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[295,442,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Monachaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in addition to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[616,787,834,859]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Goniodiscaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[616,787,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Goniodiscaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[844,950,834,859]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" genus="Anthenea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[844,950,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Anthenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent genera intermediate between the 
<taxonomicName box="[151,292,870,895]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Oreasteridae</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mah &amp; Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[396,555,870,895]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
, and as such have been transferred between the two groups throughout their taxonomic history. Based on the abactinal-facing superomarginals, and the paired, interradial abactinal plate pattern similar to those of 
<emphasis box="[464,569,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Stellaster</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollfus" authorityYear="1936" box="[630,791,942,967]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Stellasteropsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[630,791,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Stellasteropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, I agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Tortonese, E." box="[961,1156,942,967]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="271 - 276" refId="ref74623" refString="Tortonese, E. (1976) Researches on the coast of Somalia. Seastars of the genus Monachaster (Echinodermata, Asteroidea). Monitore Zoologico Italiano, New Series, Supplemento VII (6), 271 - 276. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03749444.1976.10736828" type="journal article" year="1976">Tortonese (1976)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Walenkamp, J. H. C." box="[1218,1436,942,967]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 86" refId="ref75148" refString="Walenkamp, J. H. C. (1990) Systematics and zoogeography of Asteroidea (Echinodermata) from Inhaca Island, Mozambique. Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 261, 1 - 86." type="journal article" year="1990">Walenkamp (1990)</bibRefCitation>
among others who have placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doderlein" authorityYear="1916" box="[505,653,978,1003]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" genus="Monachaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[505,653,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Monachaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mah &amp; Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[779,934,978,1003]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
rather than the 
<taxonomicName box="[1110,1256,978,1003]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Oreasteridae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1436,834,1111]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Some characters, such as the, dense granular covering, the minimal adambulacral spination and the bald patches on the superomarginals, also suggest 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doderlein" authorityYear="1916" box="[664,812,1050,1075]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" genus="Monachaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[664,812,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Monachaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows affinities with the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mah" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1103,1223,1050,1075]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ferdininae">Ferdininae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mah &amp; Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1238,1397,1050,1075]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
) as described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mah, C. L." box="[300,436,1086,1111]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref72305" refString="Mah, C. L. (2017) Overview of the Ferdina - like Goniasteridae (Echinodermata: Asteroidea) including a new subfamily, three new genera and fourteen new species. Zootaxa, 4271 (1), 1 - 72. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4271.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Mah (2017)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
